<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Macroscopic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Cap 1.0-4.1 cm in diameter, convex, sometimes umbonate, margin involute, rarely sulcate, tacky when moist, sometimes hygrophanous, uniformly colored or variably bicolored, at center umber to sepia (6E6, 6E7, 6F6, 6F7), margin cream to pinkish-buff to ochraceous or dark olive buff (4A2, 4A3, 5A3, 5B3, 5B5, 5C5); remains of universal veil sometimes present; partial veil present. Lamellae adnate or adnexed to emarginate, pale brown, maximum depth 3-5 mm, number of lamellae {L} 40-48, droplets usually absent, but occasionally visible with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10 lens, white fimbriate edge usually present, but sometimes indistinctly. Stem 1.3-7.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.6 cm, 4.5-7.3(-8) cm at base, stem Q 3.3-15.5(-18), at first whitish fibrillose becoming pale brown, base cylindrical to clavate or bulbous, usually pruinose or floccose at apex. Context firm, stem inside stuffed, later hollow, stem flesh discoloring from base, sometimes weakly. Smell raphanoid, sometimes with hints of cocoa. Taste mild to bitter, usually raphanoid. Spore deposit brownish olive (5E5).
</paragraph>
