<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Microscopic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Spores amygdaloid or limoniform, occasionally appearing ovoid or fusoid, on ave. 10.5-12.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.0-6.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ave. Q 1.6-2.1, very weakly ornamented (O1O2), perispore not or somewhat loosening (P0P1), rather strongly dextrinoid (D2D3), yellow to yellow brown, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
guttulate, papillate. Basidia 23-32(-36) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ave. Q = 2.6-4.4, mostly four-spored. Cheilocystidia lageniform to ventricose, occasionally cylindrical, occasionally with a characteristic thickening, apically, basically or medially, sometimes geniculate or septate, on ave. 41-60 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6 (apex) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5.5 (middle) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.5-12 (base) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ratios A/M = 0.93-1.25, A/B = 0.45-0.76, B/M = 1.58-2.31. Epicutis an ixocutis, 125-170 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick (measured from exsiccata), maximum hyphae width 3.5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, sometimes encrusted, shape of trama elements beneath subcutis sausage-shaped, up to 14 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. Caulocystidia similar to cheilocystidia, but usually less ventricose, up to 120 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="collections examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Collections examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">S-Greenland</emphasis>
: Paamiut, W of the Navigation School area, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="62" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55555" value="62.0">62°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="49.67" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="-49.67">49.67°W</geoCoordinate>
, 7 Sep 1990, T. Borgen (TB90.100, C-F-119760), 20 m, with 
